Sen. Patty Murray (D-Washington), the top Democratic appropriator in the Senate, said Wednesday that President Donald Trump’s freeze on federal grants funding — which a judge temporarily blocked Tuesday — is jeopardizing negotiations over government funding. Currently, Congress has a deadline of March 14 to fund the government, but Murray said it is “extremely difficult to agree to a compromise on anything if the White House is going to assert that they control the funds.”
“This is really putting that in jeopardy,” she added.
